The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Ludhiana, April 12 (PTI): Three policemen were today arrested and sacked for allegedly raping a 16-year-old in a park behind the deputy commissioners residence.          
	The incident took place last night when the girl from Lucknow went to meet her friend in the park, police said. She was overpowered by the three policemen and taken to a corner. The policemen forcibly took away her friend, gagged him and allegedly raped her. A medical examination confirmed the raped.                  
	London (PTI): A Sikh shopkeeper in Suffolk has chased a hooded attacker out of his shop with a bottle of wine , undeterred by a knife brandished by the thug. The incident, captured on the stores CCTV, earned him praise from the local community.                   
	Mumbai (PTI): An eight-year-old boy was killed and three persons injured after a speeding jeep rammed into a public booth in central Mumbai on Saturday. The boy was inside the booth along with family members when the Tata Sumo slammed into it, police said.                   
	Kochi (PTI): A 19-year-old has been sentenced to death for murdering a lawyer who had employed him last year. Amal Raj had withdrawn Rs 6 lakh from the lawyers bank account using his chequebook following which he planned the murder. Two other accused  Rajesh (21) and Shimon (23)  were sentenced for life.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): A 70-year-old woman has approached the deputy commissioner of police alleging local cops had refused to lodge her complaint against her son. She said her son tried to set her ablaze last month over a property dispute. She also complained against the police in Wadala who had declined to lodge the FIR saying no case was made out yet.                  
	New Delhi: A 25-year-old Dalit was shot at allegedly over family rivalry on Saturday, sparking tension at Loni on the outskirts of Delhi. Jagmohan was shot at twice and is battling for life in hospital. Two persons have been arrested.                                                                                                                         
